STEP 0 - Create an account on GitHub [if you do not have one already]

STEP 1 - Create a Personal Access Token on Github

STEP 1.1 - Creating a personal access token:
In the upper-right corner of any page, click your profile photo, then click Settings.
In the left sidebar, click Developer settings.
In the left sidebar, click Personal access tokens.
Click Generate new token.
Give your token a descriptive name.

STEP 2 - Create your first repository

STEP 3 - Clone your repository
On the terminal, do the following:

STEP 3.1 - Clone your repository
root@896cf839cf9a:/# git clone https://{YOUR_PERSONAL_TOKEN}@github.com/{YOUR_USERNAME}/testing_course.git                  
Cloning into 'testing_course'...
warning: You appear to have cloned an empty repository.       
Replace {YOUR_PERSONAL_TOKEN} with your token from step 1

Replace {YOUR_USERNAME} with your username from step 0 and 1

STEP 6 - Create the README.md and push the modifications
Navigate to this new directory. Tips
root@896cf839cf9a:/# cd testing_course/
root@896cf839cf9a:/testing_course#

